### Kaptai Tourist API — request collection
# IntelliJ / VS Code "REST Client" format. Every route is nested under an
# `Accept: application/json` predicate, so that header is always required.

@baseUrl = http://localhost:9090/api/v1
@hotelId = 1111

### Public — browse all hotels (no token)
GET {{baseUrl}}/hotel
Accept: application/json

### Public — search hotels by name (case-insensitive substring)
GET {{baseUrl}}/hotel?search=lakeside
Accept: application/json

### Public — paginated hotel list
GET {{baseUrl}}/hotel?page=0&size=10
Accept: application/json

### Public — filter hotels having ALL given facilities (repeat facility=), + name + paging
GET {{baseUrl}}/hotel?facility=FACILITY_ID_1&facility=FACILITY_ID_2&search=lake&page=0&size=10
Accept: application/json

### Public — hotels with a room free for these dates (+ guests, combinable with search/facility/paging)
GET {{baseUrl}}/hotel?checkIn=2026-08-01&checkOut=2026-08-04&guests=2&page=0&size=10
Accept: application/json

### Owner/Admin — hotel dashboard (needs a token for an owner of this hotel, or an admin)
# @token = paste the JWT from POST /auth/login
GET {{baseUrl}}/hotel/{{hotelId}}/dashboard
Accept: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Admin — platform-wide dashboard (admin token required)
GET {{baseUrl}}/admin/dashboard
Accept: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Any authenticated user — change own password
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/change-password
Accept: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "currentPassword": "secret123",
  "newPassword": "newSecret456"
}

### Public — get one hotel by id (no token)
GET {{baseUrl}}/hotel/{{hotelId}}
Accept: application/json

### ─────────────── NestJS-parity additions ───────────────

### Public — welcome smoke test
GET {{baseUrl}}/welcome
Accept: application/json

### Public — login by mobile (instead of email)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Accept: application/json
Content-Type: application/json

{ "mobile": "+8801700000000", "password": "secret123" }

### Public — register as owner (creates USER + PENDING enlistment request)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register-owner
Accept: application/json
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Owner One", "email": "owner1@example.com", "mobile": "+8801711111111",
  "gender": "MALE", "password": "secret123",
  "hotelName": "Lakeside Retreat", "message": "Please enlist my hotel"
}

### Admin — list owner requests (optional ?status=PENDING|APPROVED|REJECTED)
GET {{baseUrl}}/owner-request?status=PENDING
Accept: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Admin — approve an owner request (grants HOTEL_OWNER)
POST {{baseUrl}}/owner-request/REQUEST_ID/approve
Accept: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Admin — reject an owner request
POST {{baseUrl}}/owner-request/REQUEST_ID/reject
Accept: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Owner/Admin — the caller's own hotels (enriched)
GET {{baseUrl}}/owner/hotel
Accept: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Admin — all hotels + owners + counts
GET {{baseUrl}}/admin/hotel
Accept: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Owner/Admin — set a hotel's cover image
POST {{baseUrl}}/image/{{hotelId}}/IMAGE_ID/primary
Accept: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Owner/Admin — set a room's cover image
POST {{baseUrl}}/hotel/{{hotelId}}/room/ROOM_ID/image/IMAGE_ID/primary
Accept: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
